O-O 9. d4 Bg4 10. d5 Na5 11. Bc2 Qc8 {This is Black's latest attempt to deal
with the Yates System. The point is to play c7-c6 and capture with the queen,
thus keeping good control of the d5-square, as well as a harmonius development.
} 12. h3 Bd7 13. Nbd2 c6 14. dxc6 Qxc6 {The main move. Let's have a look at
the alternatives:} (14... Bxc6 {is a bit illogical after having played Qc8 but
still playable.} 15. Nf1 {White has the idea of Bg5-Ne3 or Ng3. Later on, he
can begin to fight for the control of the center. Here, Black has tried few
different moves. Let's have a look at the two more logical ones:} Nc4 (15...
Re8 16. Bg5 $5 {standard play. The f6-knight is an important piece so it is
useful to have it under some pressure. 16.Ng3 is also a valid option} (16. Ng3
g6 17. Bg5 Qe6 18. b3 Bf8 19. Qd2 Nd7 20. Be3 $14 {Saptarshi,R (2476)-Yang
