20. Qd2 $14 {In the future White can start playing on the kingside. The
advance c3-c4 is also an option is some cases.}) 17. b3 Rac8 18. Qd2 (18. Ng3
$5) 18... Nh5 19. g4 Nf6 (19... Nf4 $5 {was possible} 20. Bxf4 exf4 21. Qxf4
Qf6 $1 22. Qe3 Bb7 23. Nd4 Nc6 24. Nf5 {Black has some compensation for the
pawn}) 20. Ng3 g6 {Andreikin,D (2723)-Grigoriants,S (2576) Minsk BLR 2017} 21.
c4 Nb7 22. cxb5 axb5 23. b4 {White's position looks promising with Bb3 coming
soon}) 16. Ng3 g6 17. Nh2 ({I think I prefer} 17. b3 Nb6 18. Bh6 Re8 19. Qd2 {
with Rad1-Nh2-Ng4 ideas}) 17... Ne8 (17... d5 $5 18. exd5 Rd8 19. b3 Nb6 20.
Qe2 Nbxd5 (20... Rxd5 21. c4 $1 $16 bxc4 22. bxc4 Rc5 23. Ba3 {or Be3 and
Black has to give up the exchange.}) 21. Qxe5 {Black is quite active and
should have enough compensation for the pawn} Bf8 22. Qg5 Bg7 23. Bd2 Nc7 24.
Rad1 Qb7 25. Ng4 Nxg4 26. Qxg4 Rxd2 27. Rxd2 Bxc3 28. Ree2 Bxd2 29. Rxd2 Re8 (
