prospects in this position and that's the reason why Beliavsky offered a draw}
20. Re3 $5 {with Rg3 next looks dangerous}) 15. Nf1 Nc4 {Black has other
interesting moves here} (15... Nb7 $5 16. Nh4 $146 {The idea of this move is
not so much to go Nf5 right away but to open way for Qf3} Nc5 17. Qf3 g6 18.
Bg5 Kg7 19. Qe3 Rfe8 20. Ng3 {alrady Nhf5+ is a threat!} Kh8 21. Rad1 Be6 22.
