Qxd5 20. Nhf5 Bf8 $4 (20... Qxd1 21. Rxd1 Bf8 22. Nh5 $1 $14) 21. Nxh6+ gxh6
22. Nh5 $1 {a nice combination} Qe6 23. Nxf6+ Qxf6 24. Qxd7 Bc5 25. Qf5 Qxf5
26. Bxf5 Rad8 27. axb5 axb5 28. Bxh6 Nxb2 29. Re4 Bf8 30. Rg4+ Kh8 31. Bxf8
Rxf8 32. Ra6 {1-0 (32) Sivanandan,B (2452) -Sriram,J (2444) Visakhapatnam 2006}
) (17... g6 $1 {is a solid choice and I think it's very difficult for White to
